exercises.name: Jumping Jacks
exercises.description: Stand with feet together, then jump while spreading arms and legs. Return to starting position and repeat.

exercises.name: Push-Ups
exercises.description: Assume a plank position, then lower body until chest nearly touches the ground. Push back up to starting position.

exercises.name: Squats
exercises.description: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, then lower body as if sitting back into an invisible chair. Return to standing position.

exercises.name: Plank
exercises.description: Assume a push-up position but with elbows bent and forearms resting on the ground. Hold this position.

exercises.name: High Knees
exercises.description: Run in place, bringing knees up towards chest as high as possible with each step.

exercises.name: Mountain Climbers
exercises.description: Assume a push-up position, then alternately drive knees towards chest in a running motion.

exercises.name: Burpees
exercises.description: From standing position, squat down, kick feet back to plank, perform a push-up, return to squat, and jump up.

exercises.name: Russian Twists
exercises.description: Sit on the floor with knees bent and feet lifted. Rotate torso to touch the ground on each side.

exercises.name: Bicycle Crunches
exercises.description: Lie on back, lift legs, and alternately bring knees towards opposite elbows while pedaling in the air.

exercises.name: Reverse Lunges
exercises.description: Step back with one leg and lower body until both knees form 90-degree angles. Return to standing position and switch legs.

exercises.name: Side Plank
exercises.description: Lie on one side with legs stacked and prop body up with elbow and forearm. Hold this position.

exercises.name: Jump Squats
exercises.description: Perform a regular squat, then jump explosively as high as possible before returning to squat position.

exercises.name: Tricep Dips
exercises.description: Sit on the edge of a chair, grip the edge, and lift body off the chair. Bend elbows and lower body, then push back up.

exercises.name: Leg Raises
exercises.description: Lie on back with legs straight and lift them towards the ceiling, then slowly lower them back down without touching the ground.

exercises.name: Shoulder Taps
exercises.description: Assume a push-up position, then alternately tap shoulders with opposite hands while keeping core stable.

exercises.name: Calf Raises
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart and lift heels off the ground, then slowly lower them back down.

exercises.name: Superman
exercises.description: Lie face down with arms extended in front. Lift arms, chest, and legs off the ground, then lower back down.

exercises.name: Jump Rope
exercises.description: Grab a jump rope and perform continuous jumps, keeping feet together and swinging the rope with wrists.

exercises.name: Single-Leg Deadlifts
exercises.description: Stand on one leg with knee slightly bent, then hinge at hips to lower torso towards the ground and extend opposite leg behind.

exercises.name: Wall Sit
exercises.description: Lean back against a wall and slide down until thighs are parallel to the ground. Hold this position.

exercises.name: Bear Crawl
exercises.description: Start on all fours with knees bent, then walk forward by moving opposite hand and foot simultaneously.

exercises.name: Flutter Kicks
exercises.description: Lie on back with legs straight and lift heels off the ground. Flutter legs up and down in small, quick motions.

exercises.name: Lateral Lunges
exercises.description: Step to the side with one leg and lower body until thigh is parallel to the ground. Return to standing position and switch legs.

exercises.name: Spiderman Plank
exercises.description: Assume a plank position, then bring knee towards elbow on the same side. Alternate sides.

exercises.name: Jumping Lunges
exercises.description: Start in a lunge position, then jump up and switch legs in mid-air before landing in a lunge on the other side.

exercises.name: Seated Leg Lifts
exercises.description: Sit on the edge of a chair with legs extended. Lift one leg up as high as possible, then lower it back down.

exercises.name: Skater Hops
exercises.description: Leap sideways from one foot to the other, swinging arms to maintain momentum.
